                            <comment id="14933329" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 28 Sep 2015 14:06:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like one line of code got deleted while adding support for other compression types:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (renameTo.endsWith(EXT_GZIP)) {
    renameTo = renameTo.substring(0, renameTo.length() - EXT_GZIP.length()); &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;// THIS LINE WAS ACCIDENTALLY DELETED
&lt;/span&gt;    compressAction = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; GzCompressAction(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; File(renameTo), &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; File(compressedName), &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;);
} &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;else&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (renameTo.endsWith(EXT_ZIP)) {
...
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14933358" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 28 Sep 2015 14:28:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It also looks like the other compression formats (other than .gz, .zip and .bz2) were not actually called during rollover... I will fix that too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14933558" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 28 Sep 2015 16:51:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed in master in commit a5447aee.&lt;br/&gt;
Enhanced existing JUnit test to deflate resulting file and verify contents.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please verify and close.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14933623" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 28 Sep 2015 17:26:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yep, it looks like I introduced this regression in commit &lt;tt&gt;7121fe223fe29db72bc7e2a9ec02248c66429790&lt;/tt&gt;. Please accept my apologies. Thank you &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=remkop%40yahoo.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;remkop@yahoo.com&quot;&gt;remkop@yahoo.com&lt;/a&gt; for fixing it AND adding a sorely missing unit test! &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14933627" author="garydgregory" created="Mon, 28 Sep 2015 17:28:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looking at this code reminds me to ask: Should we provide a more &quot;plugin-ish&quot; way to specify compression algorithms?&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="14933723" author="remkop@yahoo.com" created="Mon, 28 Sep 2015 18:26:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The new code now loops over the compression formats defined in the enum. I think that if we add any more formats not supported by commons.compress we may need more code changes anyway. For now I think we&apos;re good.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
